{
  "texts": [
    "• Passive: the most limited sort of interaction, as the user can only observe events with the HMD.",
    "• Interactive: the user can interact with the environment, but cannot move freely.",
    "• Explorative: free exploration is allowed, though no direct interaction with the environment.",
    "• Explorative with interaction: the most complete type of interaction, as the user can explore freely and interact directly with the environment.",
    "Physiological studies can cast light on bodily functions, cellular reactions, human organs, and tissues, among many other aspects (Moro et al. 2021)."
  ]
}